# this card is relevant to the various economic plans of possible ministers

= Enacting [+ minister_for_economy +]'s Plan

[? if biya_economics = 1: Jean Biya's economic plan relies on three major prongs, the first being the mechanisation of Sahellan agriculture, the second being the creation of a pro-business environment and also the incentivisation of major industrialisation through the creation of 'speacial tax zones' or STZ's which should atract investment from foreign powers. ?][? if daouda_economics = 1: John Daouda's economic plan requires the cooperation of a swathe of various government departments, however with control of the Ministry for the Economy he can enact his proposed aquisition of derelict French businesses and lands as well as reduce the tax burdan of small farmers to increase the economic development of Sahella more evenly.?][? if njume_economics = 1: Peter Njume's ascension to the Economic Ministry means that he can enact his plan to both industrialise and socialise the economy.?][? if iswana_economics = 1: For Georges Iswana's economic plan of 'managed capitalism' to be fully realised control of the agricultural ministry will be necessary, in the meantime Iswana can implement a variety of pro-rural decisions.?]

Beyond enacting [+ minister_for_economy +]'s plan the ministry for the Economy can also make policy decisions pertaining to taxes on the poor, middle class, wealthy and corporations. As well as managing the funding of various welfare and other programs.


